      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is doing something weird. the fan is making this loud humming sound but the blades arent actually spinning. what could be causing that and is it safe to go out there and look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming sound with no spinning blades on an AC unit is a classic sign of a mechanical issue, like a seized motor or a bad capacitor. It's probably not a catastrophic failure, but it definitely needs attention before it becomes a bigger, more expensive problem. It's not safe to just poke around with a screwdriver if you're not familiar with electrical components, so I'd recommend calling a professional technician. They can diagnose the problem safely and get your cooling system running again.",
